import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
    title="About Calculemus"
    description="The AI Team of Leiden University - Shaping the future of artificial intelligence with positive impact."
    pubDate={new Date('May 08 2026')}
    heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
    <p>
        <strong>"Calculemus"</strong> — <em>Let us calculate.</em> This was the famous phrase of philosopher and mathematician Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz, who dreamed of a universal language that could solve any problem simply by performing calculations. Today, we put that dream into practice, but with neural networks, data, and algorithms.
    </p>

    <p>
        We are the official AI team of <strong>Leiden University (LIACS)</strong>, run by and for passionate IT students. Our mission is not only to explore the boundaries of artificial intelligence but to do so with a sharp focus on positive societal impact.
    </p>

    <h3>Navigating the AI Challenges</h3>
    <p>
        The rise of AI brings unprecedented opportunities, but also complex challenges. How do we prevent bias in our datasets? How do we make 'black box' algorithms transparent and explainable? Within Calculemus, we dive into these issues. We don't blindly build the next hype; instead, we analyze architectures, optimize efficiency, and design solutions that move humanity forward.
    </p>

    <h3>Building a Community</h3>
    <p>
        Knowledge is only valuable when shared. That is why Calculemus acts as the connecting factor for AI enthusiasts inside and outside the university. We believe the best ideas emerge when different perspectives come together in one room.
    </p>
    <p>
        Throughout the year, we organize various events to turn theory into practice:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Tech Talks & Guest Lectures:</strong> Insights from leading researchers and industry experts.</li>
        <li><strong>Hackathons:</strong> 24-hour sprints where we use AI to solve real-world problems.</li>
        <li><strong>Coding Nights:</strong> Hands-on sessions where we train, debug, and optimize models together in a relaxed setting.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Join the Computation</h3>
    <p>
        Whether you are a seasoned Machine Learning engineer or a first-year student who just wrote their first Python script: there is a place for you in our network. Keep an eye on our <a href="/events">Events</a> page for upcoming meetups and join the discussion.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        <em>The future isn't just predicted; it's computed. Let's compute it together.</em>
    </p>
</Layout>